<p>I am using cordova-plugin-dialogs plugin for my mobile app. The dialog can be displayed via something like this:</p>  <pre><code>$cordovaDialogs.confirm('We could not reach the server. Please try again.', 'Network Problem', ['Cancel','Retry'])     .then(function(buttonIndex) {         if(buttonIndex==2){             checkNetwork();         }else{             navigator.app.exitApp();         } }); </code></pre>  <p>It works, but the problem is when user "click" outside the dialog, the dialog will disappear and trigger the result of <code>0</code> and the app will exit. How can I disable ability to "click" outside of the dialog?</p>